        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 10:24AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1024 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bemis, or 8 miles south of Jackson, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Neely, Pinson, Bemis, Cedar Grove, Beech Bluff, Jackson, Westover,
Madison Hall, Juno, Gilmore, Maple Grove, Blue Goose, East Union,
Pinson Mounds State Archaeological Park, Malesus, Claybrook, Medon,
Parkburg, Huron, and Russell Crossroads.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT for
west Tennessee.</instruction>
